### Seven Sources of Waste (Muda)


1.	Overproduction. - Mismatch between supply and demand. To produce sooner or in greater quantities than         customers requires.
2.	Transportation. - Unnecessary movement of parts or people between processes.
3.	Rework. - Repeating or correcting an operation because of quality problems. “Do it right at the first time”
4.	Over-processing. - Processing beyond what the customer requires.
5.	Motion. - Unnecessary movement of parts or people within a process. 
6.	Inventory. - The worst source of waste. Number of flow units in the system.  For physical products: raw  material, work in progress or finished products.
7.	Waiting. - Underutilizing people e or parts while a process completes a work cycle,
